# Authentik Automation Verification

ChimerAI deploys Authentik, wires Traefik forward-auth middleware, and
automates Authentik proxy providers, applications, and embedded outpost
membership for ChimerAI-managed apps that require ingress auth.

## Admin URL

```text
https://{{ chimerai_authentik_host }}/
```

Bootstrap email:

```text
{{ chimerai_authentik_bootstrap_email }}
```

## Managed Applications

ChimerAI expects these Authentik applications and proxy providers to exist:

{% for app in chimerai_authentik_managed_proxy_apps %}
- Application: `{{ app.name }}` (`{{ app.slug }}`)
- Provider: `{{ app.provider_name }}`
- External URL: `{{ app.external_url }}`
{% else %}
- No Authentik-managed protected applications are enabled.
{% endfor %}

## Outpost

The managed providers should be attached to:

```text
{{ chimerai_authentik_outpost_name }}
```

The outpost `authentik_host` should be:

```text
https://{{ chimerai_authentik_host }}
```

## Traefik Middleware

The Traefik middleware expected by ChimerAI is named:

```text
authentik@docker
```

For each protected app, verify the Traefik router uses `websecure`, TLS, the
configured certificate resolver, and this middleware. Also verify the app host
has an outpost route for `/outpost.goauthentik.io/`.

## Manual Tasks

ChimerAI does not automate users, groups, policies, external identity
providers, OAuth clients, app-specific authorization rules, DNS, firewall
policy, or the switch from Let's Encrypt staging to production certificates.
Configure those after the automated application/provider/outpost wiring is
present and verified.
